translated: Frennesen, Torsten Rye, civil engineer, Borås, b. May 20th, 1885 in Malmköping, Södermanland. Son of county veterinarian Nils Oscar Rye F. and Gerda Charlotta Paulina Berg. Married to Elsa Jonzon in 1914. Graduated from Halmstad's High School and CTI (E) in 1905, and received an engineering degree from Polytechnicum in Zurich in 1908. Worked in Finland, Norway, Denmark, Germany, Switzerland, Italy, Belgium, England, France, Spain, Lithuania, Latvia, Cuba, the USA, Canada, and Mexico. Worked as a line engineer at Kraft-Übertragungswerke Rheinfelden in Baden from 1908-1909, as a montage engineer at ASEA in Västerås from 1909-1911, as the head of the electronic department at John M. Sumner & Co. in Mexico from 1911-1913, as an employee at the export department at ASEA in Västerås from 1913-1914, as the head of the ASEA branch in Norrköping from 1914-1919, as the purchasing manager at ASEA in Västerås from 1919-1922, as the sales manager at Standard Varnish Works in Stockholm from 1922-1924, as the sales manager at Elektromek. Ind. A-B in Helsingborg from 1924-1926, and as the chief of Lithuanian Match Company for general consul T. Kreuger and Swedish Match AB from 1926-1930. Held various positions in Stockholm from 1930-1933, worked as the district manager for Livförsäkr. A-B Victoria's savings department in Borås in 1933, and served as a representative for Städernas Allm. Brandstodsbol. and others since 1936. Torsten was a member of the Swedish Technical Association since 1916, as well as the Freemasons and Rotary Club.
